{
  "texts": [
    "28 Safety regulations often mandate that firms take steps to enhance product safety, reducing the relevance of product liability when both safety regulations and market forces ensure safe products (Polinsky & Shavell, 2010, 1441-1442).",
    "This essentially shifts the responsibility to the certification stage.",
    "29 Sector-specific regulators with industry expertise may be better suited than courts to determine when, to whom, and what obligations should be imposed.",
    "28 If for-profit entities offer voluntary certification, a possible downside is that the certifier provides only minimal information.",
    "The economic argument is that the certifier is incentivised to certify products only above some bare minimum threshold but will not provide more detailed information to users (Lizzeri, 1999)."
  ]
}